# Irys SDK Upload Example

Based on the README provided, here's how to set up Node.js uploads:

## Installation

```bash
npm install @irys/sdk
```

## Upload Code

```javascript
const getIrys = async () => {
	const providerUrl = "https://rpc-mumbai.maticvigil.com";
	const token = "matic";

	const irys = new Irys({
		network: "devnet",
		token,
		key: process.env.PRIVATE_KEY,
		config: { providerUrl },
	});
	return irys;
};

const uploadData = async () => {
	const irys = await getIrys();
	const dataToUpload = "GM world.";
	try {
		const receipt = await irys.upload(dataToUpload);
		console.log(`Data uploaded ==> https://gateway.irys.xyz/${receipt.id}`);
	} catch (e) {
		console.log("Error uploading data ", e);
	}
};
```

**Note:** The documentation states this SDK is "deprecated and are no longer actively supported." The README recommends migrating to the newer Irys platform instead. The provided example doesn't specify free tier limitations—check current Irys documentation for upload restrictions.

